snippet: Takata Corp, the Japanese auto parts maker at the center of a global vehicle recall, ordered its technicians to destroy results of tests on some of its air bags after finding cracks in air bag inflators, the New York Times said on Friday....

headline.print_headline: Takata Executives Ordered Technicians to Erase Air Bag Test Results: Report
headline.main: Takata Executives Ordered Technicians to Erase Air Bag Test Results: Report

lead_paragraph: Takata Corp, the Japanese auto parts maker at the center of a global vehicle recall, ordered its technicians to destroy results of tests on some of its air bags after finding cracks in air bag inflators, the New York Times said on Friday.
